Description:
This lab is vulnerable to Server-Side Template Injection (SSTI).
The goal is to identify the template engine, achieve code execution, and delete the target file.

Steps to Solve:
1️-Identify the Injection Point
-Log in using:
content-manager:C0nt3ntM4n4g3r
-Navigate to product templates and edit a product description.
-Notice the template syntax:
${someExpression}

2️-Identify the Template Engine
-Inject an invalid expression:
${foobar}
-Save the template and observe the error message.
-The error reveals that the application is using Freemarker.

3️-Research Exploitation Method
-From Freemarker documentation:
The new() built-in can instantiate Java objects.
-From JavaDoc:
Look at classes implementing TemplateModel.
-Find the class:
freemarker.template.utility.Execute
-This class allows execution of system commands.

4️-Achieve Remote Code Execution (RCE)
-Use the Execute class with new():
<#assign ex="freemarker.template.utility.Execute"?new()> ${ ex("rm /home/carlos/morale.txt") }

5️-Exploit the Vulnerability
-Replace the previous invalid payload with:
<#assign ex="freemarker.template.utility.Execute"?new()> ${ ex("rm /home/carlos/morale.txt") }
-Save the template.
-Reload the product page.

Result:
-Arbitrary command execution achieved
-File deleted:
/home/carlos/morale.txt
